description: Lists the queues associated with a routing profile.

parameters.name: InstanceId
parameters.description: The identifier of the Amazon Connect instance. You can find the instance ID in the Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the instance.

parameters.name: RoutingProfileId
parameters.description: The identifier of the routing profile.

nested_items.name: NextToken
nested_items.description: If there are additional results, this is the token for the next set of results.

nested_items.name: QueueArn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the queue.

nested_items.name: Priority
nested_items.description: The order in which contacts are to be handled for the queue. For more information, see Queues: priority and delay.

nested_items.name: Delay
nested_items.description: The delay, in seconds, that a contact should be in the queue before they are routed to an available agent. For more information, see Queues: priority and delay in the Amazon Connect Administrator Guide.

nested_items.name: LastModifiedTime
nested_items.description: The timestamp when this resource was last modified.

nested_items.name: LastModifiedRegion
nested_items.description: The Amazon Web Services Region where this resource was last modified.
